{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/2015-02-24-sluggish-internet-explorer-performance-and-browser-link/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"tjrobinson.net","author":"Tom Robinson"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"2882a199-4faf-5cc9-bef7-2e2036dc5995","excerpt":"I recently experienced problems where Internet Explorer performance was sluggish, almost unusable. I could barely log in to the application I was running as…","html":"<p>I recently experienced problems where Internet Explorer performance was sluggish, almost unusable. I could barely log in to the application I was running as there was a long lag between key presses and the text appearing. It turns out that the culprit was Browser Link, a new feature in Visual Studio 2013 that creates a communication channel between the development environment and one or more web browsers.</p>\n<p>Disabling Browser Link solved the performance problems.</p>\n<p>Uncheck the “Enable Browser Link” option:</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 399px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/88d5eeb799275415606342a5f4a9b081/a307d/Untitled.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 50.67567567567568%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Visual Studio screenshot\"\n        title=\"Visual Studio screenshot\"\n        src=\"/static/88d5eeb799275415606342a5f4a9b081/a307d/Untitled.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/88d5eeb799275415606342a5f4a9b081/12f09/Untitled.png 148w,\n/static/88d5eeb799275415606342a5f4a9b081/e4a3f/Untitled.png 295w,\n/static/88d5eeb799275415606342a5f4a9b081/a307d/Untitled.png 399w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 399px) 100vw, 399px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>","frontmatter":{"title":"Sluggish Internet Explorer performance and Browser Link","date":"February 2015"}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/2015-02-24-sluggish-internet-explorer-performance-and-browser-link/","previous":{"fileAbsolutePath":"/home/runner/work/tjrobinson.net/tjrobinson.net/content/blog/2015-01-10-my-magic-lantern-bricking-experience/index.md","fields":{"slug":"/2015-01-10-my-magic-lantern-bricking-experience/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"My Magic Lantern bricking experience"}},"next":{"fileAbsolutePath":"/home/runner/work/tjrobinson.net/tjrobinson.net/content/blog/2015-03-11-404-error-accessing-salesforce-oauth2-endpoints/index.md","fields":{"slug":"/2015-03-11-404-error-accessing-salesforce-oauth2-endpoints/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"404 error accessing Salesforce OAuth2 endpoints?"}}}},"staticQueryHashes":[]}